observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the following department heads for the compliance with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015:
Inventory Committee
Complete the conduct and inventory of local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction;
Prepare the Report on Physical Count of the Road Network System of the LGU; (Annex C of the Circular)
Municipal GSO-Designate
Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; (Annex E of the Circular)
Municipal Engineer
Provide the MA and the MGSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
Municipal Accountant
Prepare the Journal Voucher to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card (Annex D of the Circular), respectively;
Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network;
Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year; and
Include a disclosure in the NTFS the total Road Network System of the LGU. (Annex B of the Circular)

We recommended that management instruct:
The MA to retrace the causes of difference and prepare the reconciliation report of the reciprocal accounts;
After the reconciliation are completed and the difference is established, instruct the MA to draw a journal voucher, record and set-up simultaneously the reciprocal account of the different funds affected and moving forward, to constantly review and analyze the transactions before these are recorded.

We recommended that LCE:
Direct the MA to verify the collectivity of the Loans Receivables Account and issue demand letters to those debtors who are still reachable;
File a request for write-off in accordance with COA Circular 2016-005 on those receivables that the collectability could not be ascertained such as the absence of records and documents to validate them or support the claims and for those debtors that can no longer be found.

We recommended that management:
To fast-track the segregation of solid waste in the sanitary land fill and to conduct information drive at the barangay level on “No Segregation, No Collection Policy” to avoid the risk of pollution that may affect public health and safety;
To make a follow-up/request the DOST for the conduct of training and other activities necessary for its actual operation.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Officer-in-Charge of the Municipal Planning and Development Office to:
Coordinate and collaborate with DOST-IX all activities to be undertaken so the program will be started;
Notify DOST-IX of any deviation in the activities and plans during the implementation of the project including deviation on the terms and conditions specifically on the rental (refund) payment schedules as provided in Annex D of the LMOA, so penalties and charges will be avoided;
Submit to DOST-IX the properly filled-up Project Information Sheet (PIS) to monitor progress of approved projects.

The Accounting Office:
Debit Due from Other Funds instead of Due to Other Funds in the GF books during remittance of taxes withheld;
Set-up proper accounting entries to adjust the negative balance of Due to Other Funds account;
Prepare a reconciliation report of the reciprocal accounts and take up the necessary adjustment in the books of accounts of the respective funds;
Instruct the Accounting personnel assigned to journalize the financial transactions to record and set-up simultaneously the reciprocal account in the different funds affected; and
Moving forward, the Municipal Accountant to constantly review the recording of such transactions.

