Designate a warehouse in-charge; and
Allow access to the warehouse facility to authorized personnel only.

In consideration of the foregoing observations, we recommend the following:
The Sangguniang Bayan to review the policy and if possible be abled to prepare a pro-forma contract of lease;
The Municipal Treasurer to duly execute all contracts of lease for all existing occupants within thirty (30) days from receipt hereof;
Management to exert extra efforts to collect receivables and impose the corresponding penalties required;
Management to create a committee to investigate the issue of sub-leasing of rental stalls;
Management to designate a market administrator from among the personnel in the Office of the Municipal Treasurer with the primary responsibility of making sure that all laws, rules and regulations pertaining to the operation, maintenance and upkeep of the municipal public market be strictly followed to avoid further problems or violations of the revenue ordinance; and
For management to fully and strictly impose all provisions of its municipal revenue code.
